England, United Kingdom","Deene, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Deene, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Hockwold cum Wilton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Hockwold cum Wilton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"la","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Hung, Cuong, Anh, Thanh, Ha, Hoang, Tuan, Chau, Hao, Hien, Hoa, Hue, Nam, Phong, Sinh, Tuong, Min, Tam, Tanh, Thai, Tham, Tinh, Yeong.  Chinese Hong, Hang, Sang, Tong, Chan, Chi, Hwa Ja, Hyung, Kam, Ki Bong, Kin, Man.","Vietnamese: from the Chinese surname 羅, see   Luo   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Lã</b>): from the Chinese surname 呂, see   Lu   6 and 3 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Luo","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Wei, Jian, Yi, Ping, Yong, Zhen, Feng, Hong, Ming, Jin, Bin, Chen, Hai, Lan, Min, Huan, Hung, Shen, Tian.","Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 羅, meaning ‘net for catching birds’ or ‘to collect’ in Chinese: (i) from Luo (羅), the name of an ancient state (located in present-day Hubei province). After it was annexed by the state of Chu during the early Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ), people from the state migrated southwards and adopted Luo (羅) as their surname. (ii) from the Po Duo Luo (破多羅) and Chi Luo (叱羅) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China, who changed their original surnames to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) from the personal name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅), leader of an ancient Turkic tribe who are believed to have migrated to China during the Tang dynasty (618–907  AD ). His descendants inherited his name Hu Se Luo (斛瑟羅) as their surname and shortened it to 羅 during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iv) from the name of one of the seven families from the Bandun Man, an ethnic group residing in ancient southwestern China (located mainly in present-day Sichuan province)."]}]},{"name":"Zouche","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alphonse, Chantal, Dominique, Francois, Herve, Michel, Rodolphe, Serge.","French (<b>Fouché</b>): variant of   Foucher  . Compare   Fooshee  ,   Foshee  ,   Fouch  , and   Foushee  .","Altered form (<b>Fouché</b>) of French   Foucher   (compare 1 above), found mainly in South Africa."],"variants":[{"name":"Foucher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Etienne, Henri, Lydie, Marcel, Rosaire.","French: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Folchari</i>, composed of the elements <i>folk</i>, <i>folc</i> ‘people’ and <i>hari</i> ‘army’. Compare   Faucher   2."]},{"name":"Foushee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1).","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its original form <i>Fouché</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Fooshee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1)."]},{"name":"Foshee","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1)."]},{"name":"Fouch","meanings":["Altered form of French <b>Fouché</b> (see   Fouche   1).","Altered form of   Fouts  , a surname of German origin.","English (of Norman origin): variant of   Fudge  ."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["equivalent of   Katherine  , also occasionally used in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Catherine la Zouche was born about 1365, in Hockwold cum Wilton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, her father, Humphrey La Zouche, was 31 and her mother, Agnes, was 16. She married John Tyndale in Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died before 1411, in Thetford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1365–Bef 1411":"umbes 1365–enne 1411","1365–1411":"1365–1411","1368–1413":"1368–1413","1395–1415":"1395–1415","1397–1426":"1397–1426","1335–1364":"1335–1364","1350–1364":"1350–1364","1395":"1395","1350":"1350","Bef 1411":"enne 1411","1426":"1426","1415":"1415","1413":"1413","1335":"1335","1368":"1368","1411":"1411","Abt 1365":"umbes 1365","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1397":"1397","after 1364":"pärast 1364","31 December 1397":"31. detsember 1397","Thetford, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Thetford, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Deene, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Deene, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hockwold cum Wilton, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Hockwold cum Wilton, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1365–Bef 1411":"noin 1365–ennen vuotta 1411","1365–1411":"1365–1411","1368–1413":"1368–1413","1395–1415":"1395–1415","1397–1426":"1